h3 Intro

p.
  The ``slide`` plugin is used to toggle whether an element is displayed or not.
  When toggled, the element slides in or out.

p.
  Combine it with the ``info-icon`` and the ``info-text`` blocks to display
  information non-intrusivevely.

h3 Example

:sample
  .l-container
    .form
      .form__group
        .form__group__label
          .info-icon(data-slide, data-target='#target')
            a.info-icon__icon
            label.info-icon__label Was wurde besch√§digt?
        .form__group__control
          input.control.control--input(type='text')
        .form__group__info-text(id='target', style='display:none;')
          .info-text
            p.
              Hallo Welt!

h3 Usage

p Activate the functionality with the data-* API

.highlight
  pre.highlight__listing.hljs: code.js
    :highlight
      <div data-slide="data-slide" data-target="#target" ...>...</div>
      <div id="target" ...>...</div>

p Activate the functionality with Javascript

.highlight
  pre.highlight__listing.hljs: code.js
    :highlight
      <div id="trigger" ...>...</div>
      <div id="target" ...>...</div>

      <script>
        $('#trigger').slide({target: '#target'})
      </script>



